It seems that President Zapatero has also understood this and his double manifesto (the reforms promised after last Saturday's meeting with the big companies and yesterday's announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite criticism of Merkel, the thesis that we must put order in the home has been opened up.
But the red line that Germany has drawn is there, and it doesn't look like they're going to move it.
