Clotilde Reiss case: Elisha has exaggerated the mediation of Syria
For more than ten months, between July 2009 and May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, the young French researcher detained in Iran for "espionage", has stunned the public in France, alerted diplomacy and accentuated the deterioration of relations between Paris and Tehran.
All under the watchful eye of American diplomats.
